<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3574] Closure.toString() calls the closure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3574</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://permalink.gmane.org/gmane.comp.lang.groovy.user/42103&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://permalink.gmane.org/gmane.comp.lang.groovy.user/42103&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When using a closure to mock an interface, it should not be called when invoking methods, that are not declared in the interface:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;==================================&lt;br/&gt;
Closure failing = {&lt;br/&gt;
      throw new RuntimeException(&quot;for test&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;interface MyType {&lt;br/&gt;
    def abc()&lt;br/&gt;
    def xyz()&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MyType instance = failing as MyType&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;// ****** all 3 calls below result in the closure to be invoked *****&lt;br/&gt;
instance.abc()&lt;br/&gt;
instance.xyz()&lt;br/&gt;
instance.toString()&lt;br/&gt;
==================================&lt;/p&gt;</description>
